caption: Friendly environment! Delicious chocolate muffin. I been there before for the donuts and they were great. But most of the time  if you dont get there early they are all gone before noon.
So fresh,  best donuts!! Yummy flavors. Especially love the glazed blueberry!!
The vegan donuts Made me have an upset stomach because something was off it didn’t sit well at all and I’ve been vegan for a few years now it had a hollow nutty aftertaste
Great donut spot, grab some coffee from frederick coffee co across the street and a donut from here

I wish I lived closer. Had an awesome doughnut that was recommended by the young lady working there. We were close in age I'm sure but had manners as if I was senior.  Definitely going back when in the area

Drove 30 mins for dough to be sold out at 11:30 on a weekday! I love this place, but selling out on a weekday before 12 is disappointing. Better luck trying Elizabeth’s Counter in VA as they usually have dough until closing and you’re pretty much guaranteed to get dough, making it worth the drive.

Bought a dozen doughnuts $42 yikes !! and then was told they require 18% gratuity.  I like to support small local businesses but.....  When I got home I tried each doughnut. They were STALE.  The only one that was fresh, was the mocha.  Dissatisfied and disappointed.

I'm always looking out for vegetarian restaurants and this one must have flown under the radar.  Food was very good, service was pleasant and efficient.  Several notes.  1. Their stock is limited, the earlier you order the better chance it will be in stock. If you do need to order later be flexible in what you want. 2. It is currently (1/2021) carry-out only so you can't easily browse the available selection in store
The butter pecan donut was one of the greatest donuts I've ever had 😍🤩🤤
Great food!

I had heard really good things about this place but in my mind I thought " Vegan Menu "? Would i like it. Let me tell you I was Blown away at how Amazing the food tasted. The service was incredible 👏 they awnsered all my questions and inquires.  WE had the iron pot Pancales we waited 30 min for them Worth it. The doughnuts were soft and airy and not super sweet. I loved that everything was reasonably priced and the service was fast. I Highly recommend and will be back very soon.
Literally drive 50 minutes, pretty much every weekend. Worth it.

Best yeast-raised donuts in the DMV, hands down. I was incredibly surprised; this shop is know for being plant-based and most vegan products I have tried are not great. I also have a hard time spending money on food if I'm not sure that it is going to "hit the spot." Glory knocked it out of the park. The donuts are amazing, but have you tried their other food?!? We had the "Just Egg" Sausage N' Cheese Sandwich -- heavenly! It tastes like the gourmet version of the Sausage Egg and Cheese McGriddle. I tried all the donuts available on the Saturday I visited. My favorite was donut filled with cold-brew cream; the bitter coffee taste balanced the sweet cream but also enhanced the flavor. During COVID, you cannot enter the restaurant and so order at the entrance. Surprisingly, not an inconvenience whatsoever! There is so much to do in this area. The neighborhood is beautiful and there are several other shops nearby to shop at. The staff are friendly and work quickly. Will be back!
Best donuts I've ever had. Friendly staff & inclusive atmosphere.

Shameful business who preys on their employees and has no problem stepping on those with disabilities.  The worst part is they paint them selfs are inclusive and caring members of the community.   With that aside their food is not good, everything has so much sugar on it and their doughnuts are over priced.  Not to mention they are a business that does gofundme's to cover operating expenses.  Go here if you support hate and want a dozen garbage Doughnuts for $30.
Donuts are made with too much dough. Don’t waste your time here. Try out some better local places! I don’t recommend and food is served cold.
We drive 60 miles each way to get their doughnuts. Needless to say, they are fantastic!
Great doughnuts. Wonderful people. I will always support businesses that do the right thing and go the extra mile. I hope everyone in Maryland supports your guys!!!
I made an hour detour last year just to come here. It was worth it. Delicious! And vegan!!
disappointed they Never update their website. I drove far to get here and they’re  randomly closed, now I have no time to grab any breakfast before my 10 hour shift at work.

Absolutely love the vegan food here and I enjoy getting to be adventurous with my donut choices/ flavors. I had the just egg n’ sausage sandwich for my breakfast this morning and it was delicious! They also make the process of ordering and picking up feel safe and easy throughout covid, and their customer service is great, with very kind employees! I definitely recommend!

These are the best vegan donuts I've had in the US! I will happily make the hour drive from Baltimore to support this awesome restaurant. Besides the donuts, it has a full breakfast and lunch menu that's entirely vegan.
Had to wait for a long time and the food was ok. Will never go back just not my type of place.

Once I had a dental appointment in Frederick downtown. I visited early in the morning and opposite to my dental care, I saw a long queue waiting outside glory donuts to open on Saturday morning. That made me curious and I bought 3 different flavored doughnuts and they were so so delicious. And I loved their service too☺️
Great business that creates new flavors and designs all the time! A staple of frederick

I was sadly disappointed with my experience at Glory Doughnuts. I came expecting to be able to dine in for breakfast, but instead had to wait outdoors in the cold since they didn’t allow indoor seating, (It’s understandable due to COVID-19, but I wish it had been stated somewhere online ahead of time.) I ordered the Huevos Rancheros; the portion was incredibly small for the price, and the taste was bland. The only thing that was tasty was the Maple Longjohn Donut. Overall, a disappointing experience, and I don’t plan to come back.
Great doughnuts and food! I ate here multiple times before I realized it was vegan! If you are looking to get non-vegans interested in vegan alternatives, this is a great place to start!

The crispy French toast felt like a complete rip off, after waiting 40 minutes my girlfriend got ONE PIECE of bread cut in half corner to corner for $10. It looked like a joke in the carryout container. I feel absolutely shafted and I think that this French toast is the worst value of any restaurant in Frederick! Most vegan restaurants I've been to give you three thick pieces of toast for the same price! This was a thin piece of wonder bread! My girlfriend and I budget to eat out only once a week to save money, and we definitely struck out this week.
Amazing plant based menu and great food!
Great place. Tasty food. I had the Monte Cristo and a cannoli doughnut. Glad to have so many vegan options to choose from, and even if you're not vegan you'll still love the food.
Fine spot for quality vegan food. I had a cousin come into town and asked me to take him back here. The bill was fair I would say.
Sooooooo good. Got there right at 9am on lovely fall Sunday morning, and were on our way with a dozen delicious donuts in less than 15 minutes.
Delicious donuts and great service! They have a great variety of fun donuts.

Today was my first visit and I wasn’t impressed at all. If you are a lover of French toast this place will hurt your damn feelings. The food was horrible and I’m a very reasonable forgiving person. I wasted over $30 at this and I’m mad about it.
Great doughnuts, great service, love supporting them. They sell out pretty fast and you might have to wait in line for a while, but they handle it well.

Worth the stop on a road trip. The donuts are good - not as good as Vegan Treats but better than any other vegan yeast donuts I've had (I don't like cake donuts at all). I saw an ingredients list that included nutmeg - I don't like nutmeg so was glad to not taste it in the dough. They were not overly greasy or heavy - they are homemade and vegan so heavier than a chain donut shop dough, but in a good way. I'd prefer slightly different flavors than what were offered but they were decent. I also had the fried ravioli and pierogi which were good if eaten hot. I feel like at least one more pierog should be included for the price. Dough dough dough. As of early September, no one is allowed in and calling ahead to order and pay seems to be the best bet.
Hands down our all time favorite doughnuts!! We have had a flavor we didn’t love.

So totally delicious. The bbq potato and bean burrito was incredible and so filling. The donuts were some of the best I have ever had. Worth the trip for anyone searching to eat healthy food that tastes amazing.

Absolutely fantastic vegan doughnuts and vegan breakfast sandwiches. My partner and I happened to come across Glory Doughnuts online and immediately had to try it out, and it did NOT disappoint. They were so kind and took our order at the door (because of COVID), and let us know how exactly long it would take to make the food. I will definitely be a frequent customer now. Thanks so much!
Delicious homemade doughnuts! The dough has a perfect chewy texture and the icing is very flavorful.

The doughnuts are amazing! Creative flavors, vegan, and delicious. I would even go as far to say these are the best doughnuts I've had since moving to Maryland. Definitely have to be there early before they sell out but it's well worth it. The food is very good as well.
Love their constantly rotating selection of tasty doughnuts. And they have the best pancakes and griddlecakes in town. Try them with blueberries or strawberries, just amazing!
Great vegan comfort food. I can eat salads/hummus at home. Bring those delicious calories and fat! They're always busy for a reason. Worth the wait and cramped dining 💯
The best vegan donuts in the DMV area. Hands down. Their breakfast options are incredible. You must check them out.
Vegan, queer, woman owned business! Food is delicious. Staff is friendly. Everything is good. Wonton burger is my fav! The pup also likes the food!
Doughnuts were not anything I would go out of my way to get. Based on Cost/taste I would rather go elsewhere. Some different flavors that I'm sure some people would enjoy.
Delicious! Worth the line! Great staff!
The donuts were good. They might be vegan Bit of sticker shock though. 2 donuts $10. Granted 2 bucks was tip but still.
Superb vegan doughnuts. Two were substantial and filling. Fresh coffee! Take out only. Phone ahead or place your order from the sidewalk. Just get there early!

My husband and i are OBSESSED with the cinnamon twist donuts! We like to treat our vegan and non vegan friends and family to these donuts when they visit us from out of town because we know they will knock their socks off. Today was my first time trying a breakfast item off of their food menu and oh did it deliver! The apple sage sausage potato melt had so much flavor I think I ate it in just a few bites.  I can’t wait to come back and try something else
Delicious vegan food. Call ahead to order if you can, it gets crowded early.

I had the chicken sandwich with orange bbq and the powdered sugar doughnuts.  It was all delicious. I just think it can be improved upon. For instance, I didn't taste the orange in the BBQ sauce on the chicken sandwich.  The powdered doughnuts should come with sort of dipping sauce. It would just take the taste of the doughnut to a new level. Right now it's just sort of boring.

Disappointed. I went there for a $4 donut before work I tried to look in their window (I had a mask on and gloves) to just see the donuts when a rude girl comes out and yells behind the cones. I explained I was just trying to look at them she said read the menu. Then when she took my order she rudely asks if I’m leaving a tip? It’s inappropriate to ask that in front of other ppl as it puts me in a forced position to tip when your donuts are already insanely expensive and all you did was throw a donut in a bag?? So I had to say yes because ppl were behind me even though  I didn’t want too. Because of her (she had black hair) I am Never going there again, save your money don’t bother here
Great donuts! Fast pick up service
Amazing. The food and donuts are to die for.
By far the best doughnuts we’ve had. Worth the trip from Tysons,VA!

Owners are the nicest people ever, the food is so good and plant based options are much appreciated, been coming here for years and you literally cant find better service, hospitality and good breakfast food, anything less than a 5 star review , is bs................
Amazing food and donuts, we had the wonton burger and blood orange donuts and they were just fantastic. Very friendly staff as well!

Nice small vegan donut shop & diner in downtown Frederick, just a few blocks from the main drag. Had a Friday lunch here and it was not too busy, the service was fast and friendly, and the food was tasty! I had the BBQ Tofu Club, it was HUGE. And the ranch they put on there was the bomb. This place is 100% vegan and 100% on my list of spots to visit again.
Delicious vegan donuts and other lunch foods
So far I like the donuts an atmosphere I come in from out of town so I am lookin at everything..I have not tried the food yet but it looks an smells delicious

I was very excited to try donuts and brunch from Glory Donuts with my husband. They were all out of donuts when we got there at 11, which I understood as they said they sell out quickly. I was most disappointed with how our brunch went. We each ordered a meal for brunch and asked for a water and a coffee. We sat down and waited for our drinks that never came, so I asked them again for a coffee and a water and she only returned with my coffee. Our meals arrived only to be lukewarm, because they had been sitting on the counter for a few minutes after the chef had said "order up". I guess the waitress wasn't paying attention. We left never having gotten our water. Staff definitely needs some training!!
Delicious... Nuff said.
They had hair in the food

Oh, man... The donuts here are just- *chef's kiss* The substantial weight of a donut from here took me by surprise. It was moist and satisfying, unlike store bought donuts. Couple it up with a cup of coffee and you are in the most wonderful state of an on the go breakfast. It's definitely packed there on the weekends and it's a small dining area but if you probably come early, you can grab seating. Will have to come back next time to try their menu!
This place is hands down amazing! Would recommend to all!
Small shop with good coffee and donuts and several breakfast offerings.

Delicious vegan food! Very friendly staff. I have never been let down by anything I've eaten here. Every flavor of donut is unique and delicious. My favorite item is the huevos rancheros with their red potatoes. Go early, they are a very busy shop.
Really nice food, it just happens to be plant-based. I really enjoy enjoyed the waffle and the chipotle potatoes. I will go again.
Blueberry muffins were delicious. Can't wait to go back and try their other options. All menu items are vegan which makes it so easy to choose from. Rather than trying to figure out what I can eat.
I love this donut place. I go here everytime I visit home in MD
Perfection. Super tasty doughnuts with a selection that includes the classics, fun ideas and a few wild cards. On the premium end for price, but its worth it

Stopped here on the way out of town. Decent selection and also tried the cold brew. Coffee was good and not too strong of a taste for being a cold brew. Doughnuts were delicious and price was about 3.50 for each of the specialty kinds. No specials on larger orders ,so a half dozen will run around $21. The maple was my favorite. Would recommend if in the area and wanted to try a quality doughnut.
Awesome food and great donuts
Delicious. Worth waiting in line.
A little bit pricey but you get what you pay for. Always delicious, and the service is great. Make sure to come early for the best selection.
Love the vibe

The food was really good! I had the special which was a waffle with vegan cheese and potatoes in the waffle. It had a spiced (smoked paprika) maple syrup. My friend had the huevos rancheros. It was topped with their tofu fried egg. If I had to guess it was either a silken tofu or soft pressed tofu. It had a good flavor, but it is very soft. I didn't mind it on the huevos rancheros or possibly on a sandwich, but for me I don't think I would care for it by itself. We grabbed some donuts to go. They were delicious, but the texture was on the bready side, not light and fluffy. They are really good with their balance of flavors. The place is tiny, with very limited seating but my friend and I managed to get a place to sit. I will definitely be eating there again when I'm in Frederick.
Love vegan food and vegan donuts.

Amazing. I love everything about this place and the people who make it happen. With a donut menu that changes day-to-day, it was easy to catch myself in here multiple times a week.  I love their Texas toast tofu scramble sandwich, it is such a greaaaat recipe!  Only downsides are: the size of the diner is a bit cramped when busy, although a great way to meet the community, and the time, very long wait time for anything from the kitchen. I would also attribute this to size as they are a small business doing their best.  ~I only mention wait time as a warning if you are in a hurry for any reason because this place is a true Frederick gem~

Amazing donuts! Not only can you not tell/taste that they’re vegan donuts, but they taste 100 times better than traditional donuts. They are soft, perfectly doughy, and wonderfully flavorful donuts. Do yourself a favor and get there early because they sell out fast. Also if you’re a therapist they give discounts to therapists... so what are you waiting for? Go get what will definitely rank as one of the best donuts you’ve ever had. Seriously.
Amazing vegan breakfast foods and top notch doughnuts!
Excellent food and donuts. Vegan and delicious. Wonderful service as well. Always busy since their food is great.
Food is amazing, I'm so happy to have flavorful vegan food and sweets!
Seriously. The best doughnuts ever!!!
Great vegan food, especially the doughnuts, and a cool space inside to eat
Good donuts, sweet
The most amazing vegan doughnuts and food EVER! So grateful for this locally owned + vegan restaurant.
Keep the salted sugar donut on the menu! So good!!
Quality and delicious
Stopped in for breakfast the other morning with my daughter. Food was delicious, especially the donuts. It’s pretty small inside but perfect for a nice little breakfast date.
Top notch doughnuts! Taste great and you wouldn't even know they're vegan.

We grabbed a dozen doughnuts here first thing in the morning and they were great. They change the flavors every day(ive heard that but not seen it since i live so far) which means you are definitely going to be able to get a variety
Fried dough was fantastic
Donuts really good, any of their filled donuts amazing!  Everything we have ordered meet our expectations,  always happy.   Small seating area, so we always get food to go.
Vegan! Friendly staff, planning to return
Just go and check it out. The food and Doughnuts are incredible. I just wish it was closer to where I lived, but always worth the drive.
The most delicious donut I have ever eaten!! Cute place too. Everyone that works there was so nice...thank you!
Good food but the inside is tiny and the employees are not very pleasant.  Some pretty good donuts though, being Vegan is what redeems it otherwise it’s nothing special.

Good doughnut and pastry.  Driving by stopped at the light and noticed a lot of foot traffic.  Had no idea the doughnuts were vegan.  Pleasantly surprised at the quality and taste.  It was later in the afternoon so the staff informed the kitchen was closing.  Was unable to try any of the prepared food.  Did try out a couple of doughnut and pastry though.
Best local donuts. Prices are great and there's plenty of seating, even a few outside. Love the ever changing daily selection of doughnuts, haven't had the same one twice.

We were headed to the area to do some hiking so I googled donuts and this place popped up. I've tried Vegan donuts before and other than the fact that they are a little chewier than regular donuts they taste pretty much the same. The shop was fairly busy when we arrived (it was a Sunday at 10 am) but I was greeted by a very helpful young man who advised me of the specials and shared his personal favorites.  I decided on 2 donuts (they do serve breakfast as well but keep in mind that seating is limited) Strawberry Frosted & a Rye Whiskey Long John. Both were very good but my favorite was the Long John, you could definitely pick up the taste of the rye whiskey, subtle and sweet. The prices are on par with what "gourmet" donuts are going for everywhere but it does keep people from picking up a dozen that's for sure. I also ordered an Orange Mango Juice thinking it would be fresh juice so I was a bit taken aback to see the clerk reach into the fridge and pour from a Trop 50 bottle of Orange Mango Juice. Bad enough I just paid $3 for a cup of juice but the artificial sweetener in the juice made it way too sweet with a horrible aftertaste. The staff is all very friendly and I think its awesome that they employ someone with special needs. The young man who greeted me came running outside when he saw our golden retriever and spent several minutes loving on him and chatting with us.

What a treat this place was after a trail run. I’m not a big one for sweets but who can resist donuts, especially one with rainbow sprinkles.  The gem of this place is that it’s vegan. Those donuts, vegan. That breakfast sandwich, vegan (eaten by my friend who says it was incredible. And the plated bakers breakfast which I devoured and was absolutely phenomenal.  I can’t wait to go back. 🤩
Donuts are good but the location lacks room and seating. Pretty expensive for what you get.
I constantly stop by getting some food in this place. I like the prompt service and well prepared dishes. Highly recommended.
So tasty!!! I got the Huevos Rancheros and we bought 6 donuts and it was lovely!

Food was outstanding and as a non vegan, I was pleasantly surprised. The reason for 3 stars however is that their customer service was lacking and that they charge $1 for a refill of an 8oz mug of coffee. Nope sorry that is too much and it isn't posted on the sign above the register, the latter being the greater offence. Also, when there are no knives in the silverware cup, the answer is not, "we're out of knives" after seeing that the cup is empty. It's "let me check the dishwasher." If you serve food that requires a knife to eat, then you need to have knives. Other downside is very limited seating, but they do the best they can with a small space. Over all? We'll probably go again, because the food and the donuts are awesome, but probably not as frequently as we would if the service was better.
Amazing vegan donuts! I was pleasantly surprised that the entire menu is vegan! I also got the fried egg tofu sandwich, the sauce on it is delicious.
This was the 1st vegan breakfast cafe I've ever been too. The "egg" platter was delicious and so were the lemon and lavender donuts. Such a yummy treat.  The staff was also very nice.
Peaches and cream donut was just as delightful as the owners.

I’m at about a 50% success rate of them being open when their business hours state. They’re closed right now (at 1:30pm) and their hours all still say “open”. Really, it’s awful. We only traveled (and wasted) half an hour, but people were at the door who had driven from Columbia specifically for these doughnuts.  What a great customer service model.

Had breakfast/brunch. Came for the Donuts but ended up getting the Huevos Rancheros. It was fantastic! So flavorful, needed absolutely nothing extra. If your on the fence with eating or trying out Vegan this would be a great place to start. I'm definitely coming back, Thank you!

Donuts were very fresh and delicious! I’ve had this place saved for a while and was passing through so I had to stop. The potatoes were perfect. Only complaint is there is no ice for beverages so my cold brew warmed up pretty quickly.
So. Damn. Good.

Simply an amazing vegan cafe in DTF. But, their donuts beat amy other yeast raised donut anywhere, vegan or otherwise! Staff is always extremely helpful and friendly! Popular flavors can run out quickly, but it's because they're scrumptious!!!

The girls who work here, work hard. Everything is made there by hand, and with care. It’s hard to run an old fashioned small business in today’s hurried world, with people who are hard to please. So go in there and support them.

I usually only get the doughnuts to go but I had a chance to have a late lunch and did a sweet and savory combination.  CRISPY STUFFED FRENCH TOAST - $10 Freshly baked Italian bread, battered and deep fried till golden.  Filled with whiskey cream and fresh berries. *suuuuper crispy french toast with a rich and creamy whiskey cream and berries, ate very sweet but enjoyed it with the organic pure maple syrup.  HOMEMADE POTATO N' ONION PEROGIES - $11 From scratch traditional perogie dough filled with mashed potatoes and caramelized onions.  Lightly fried, sprinkled with cracked peppercorn and served with creamy dill dipping sauce. *didn't really taste any of the caramelized onions but the mashed potatoes were nice and creamy inside of a crispy perogie crust.

Not sure why I ever bother trying to come here. The food is great, but it's not worth the trip. I travel about 25 minutes just to visit this place, and on three separate occasions, I've walked through the front door just to be told they're closing. I always check the hours before I go, and have always arrived over an hour before closing time. I wish someone would teach them how to update the hours that they set on their Google listing if they're going to change them.
Always seems to be closed or out of doughnuts! They now close at 3...
These vegan donuts are okay...they're just missing something.
Wonderful unique local business owned by old friends so I might be biased, but their donuts are wondeful and their food menu is fabulous!
Amazing ood! I've made the drive from Harrisburg, Pa several times because it is worth it for delicious vegan food!

My manager brought a couple dozen doughnuts from here, and they are legitimately the best I’ve ever had. A coworker and I were talking about how good vegan food had gotten in recent years, when another person walked around and told us how horrible vegans were... he wouldn’t speak to us the rest of the day when we told him the doughnuts he was shoving his face full of were vegan!
Everything here is so good, even my non-vegan family loves it.
They change s there hours and didn’t bother to go online and change them on googleyelp. Passing through town and parked far away to do your w this as my goal. Sad.
Cute spot! Im not vegan so I am usually not inclined to eat at vegan places. I decided to try It out and the donuts are REALLY good. Im glad I went!

Creative vegan doughnuts that deliver that sweet sweet mouthwatering 🍩😋👋🤤😃🍩😋👋🤤... After trying to resist more be sure to check out their delicious and filling breakfast options as well. I’ve enjoyed the Tofu Fried Egg Sandwhich and Pancakes. Definitely going to try the Salted Apple Pie Stuffed French Toast next time;) Side note, Good food for hangovers, which also explains cooking style. But hey, the name isn’t Glory🍩Doughnuts for nothing! Go and set your taste buds free to explore the new world of doughnuts that await!
Great food and staff with vegan friendly options.  Took me a while to find a seat because it's a small space inside and limited seating outside.  Love the concept and the food!

Some of the best doughnuts I've had, plant-based or otherwise. The atmosphere is inclusive, the staff friendly, and the food delicious. Be sure to get there early before all the doughnuts sell out and follow them on instagram to stay up-to-date on flavors of the day and specials.
This place is absolutely amazing!!! Very tasty doughnuts, but even better breakfast and lunch foods. Would love to go again!
Love love love glory doughnuts. Their food is always amazing and their donut flavors are so creative. Brought my vegan friend here for the first time, he was blown away!
The best doughnuts EVER!
